# .codedna — CodeDNA project manifest
project: codedna
description: "An In-Source Communication Protocol for AI Coding Agents — spec, benchmark, tools"
version: "0.7"

packages:
  benchmark_agent/swebench/:
    purpose: "Multi-model SWE-bench benchmark runner and result analyzer"
    key_files: [run_agent_multi.py, analyze_multi.py, annotator.py, setup_agent_annotated.py]

  benchmark_agent/projects_swebench/:
    purpose: "5 Django SWE-bench tasks with control/ and codedna/ variant dirs"
    depends_on: [benchmark_agent/swebench/]

  integrations/:
    purpose: "AI tool integration files — CLAUDE.md, .cursorrules, copilot-instructions.md"

  tools/:
    purpose: "AST-based auto-annotator for existing codebases"
    key_files: [auto_annotate.py]

  paper/:
    purpose: "Scientific paper — EN and IT HTML versions + whitepaper"

cross_cutting_patterns: {}

agent_sessions:
  - agent: claude-sonnet-4-6
    provider: anthropic
    date: 2026-03-20
    session_id: s_20260320_001
    task: "design v0.8 features: message: field, git telemetry, verification agents"
    changed:
      - SPEC.md
      - README.md
      - integrations/CLAUDE.md
      - paper/codedna_paper.html
      - paper/codedna_paper_IT.html
      - paper/codedna_whitepaper_EN.html
      - .codedna
    visited:
      - SPEC.md
      - README.md
      - integrations/CLAUDE.md
      - paper/codedna_paper.html
      - paper/codedna_paper_IT.html
      - paper/codedna_whitepaper_EN.html
      - benchmark_agent/swebench/run_agent_multi.py
      - benchmark_agent/swebench/analyze_multi.py
      - benchmark_agent/swebench/annotator.py
      - benchmark_agent/swebench/setup_agent_annotated.py
      - tools/auto_annotate.py
    message: >
      Designed v0.8 features in collaboration with Fabrizio:
      (1) message: field — agent-to-agent conversational layer at Level 1 and Level 2,
      lifecycle: observation → rules: promotion or dismissal, append-only.
      (2) Git trailers as audit log — AI-Agent:, AI-Provider:, AI-Session:, AI-Visited:,
      AI-Message: — git is the authoritative history, .codedna is the lean cache.
      (3) Verification agent integration — 5 audit types enabled by git telemetry:
      navigation correctness, rule compliance, annotation accuracy, message: lifecycle,
      navigation efficiency per model.
      (4) Title updated across all files to "CodeDNA: An In-Source Communication Protocol
      for AI Coding Agents".
      Next: test whether this methodology actually improves development of this repo itself.
      .codedna created for the first time — this is session 001.
